postcontent:

This is a Winchester Model 1873 .22 Short Rifle that I inherited from my Grandfather. It was purchased by my Great Grandfather when it was brand new and was used as a farm gun on a routine basis. The barrel has a dovetail mounted sporting style front sight with silver bead and a sporting style rear sight. The barrel, magazine, forearm cap and receiver appear to have had the bluing stripped off and the hammer, lever and crescent buttplate are casehardened. This is law enforcement duty ammo new in the box. auction is for five boxes, 250 rounds. Speer Gold Dot Ammunition continues dominating the law enforcement community. Its proven reliability for tough jobs has made it the #1 duty ammunition on the market today. To put it simply, it's the best. Gold Dot was the first high-performance handgun ammunition to be loaded with true, bonded-core bullets. Using our exclusive Uni-Cor process, we bond the jacket to the core one molecule at a time. This virtually eliminates core-jacket separation, the leading cause of handgun bullet failures and often inherent in the design of conventional bullets. Our bonding happens at the beginning of the bullet making process, exactly where it should. We form the hollow point cavity in two stages. The first establishes how far the bullet can expand; the second controls the rate of expansion. This patented* two-step cavity formation gives Speer engineers incredible control in the design process. Each bullet caliber and weight is tuned for optimum expansion and penetration. The bullet is finished to provide a smooth profile for reliable feeding in semi-auto handguns. Gold Dot is assembled in quality brass cases, nickelplated for smooth feeding and protection from corrosion. For sure-fire ignition under real-world conditions, we use famous CCI primers. Then we load select, low-flash propellants matched to the performance needs of each cartridge. We put a lot of thought into each Gold Dot cartridge so you no longer have to.

title: For Sale:  Winchester 22 Short Rifle, Pump, Model 1890 SN: 255135
postcontent:
This rifle is a Winchester 22 short, pump action.  Model number 1890 and serial number 255135.  As far as I can research it seems to have been made in 1905.  My husbands uncle gave it to him when he was about 10 (he is now 76).  

The rifle is in decent shape with some expected wear and tear on the wood stock.  There are two screws missing, one on the pump handle and one on the trademark plate.  There are two marks on the lock just above the hammer and my husband thinks they are shot marks.  Also, the extractor is worn so the spent cartridges won't extract.  The last time we shot this rifle was about seven years ago.

The rifle has been cleaned through the years but we have not cleaned it in the most recent years.  A man who regularly goes to gun shows told us not to "clean it up" before we try to sell it at a gun show, which we haven't gone to as of yet, so we have not given the rifle a good cleaning.  Having said that, it's has been in our closet for years so it just need a little attention!

This is the real deal original CAR-15!!! This is one of the nicest and best quality ARs you can buy. And to get a new, unfired one is very rare. The serial number is V followed by 4 digits. You can confirm the manufacture date on Oly Arms website "What does my serial number mean" webpage. 

This has the impossible to find 11.5 barrel with 5.5 permanently attached supressor making it meet the 16" barrel length requirement. This is an extremely rare rifle!
